- Wed 18 Dec 2019. Butembo: new case after 55 days
[Radio Okapi, in French, machine trans., edited]
https://www.radiookapi.net/2019/12/18/actualite/sante/nord-kivu-un-nouveau-cas-debola-notifie-butembo-55-jours-apres

A new case of Ebola is reported Monday [16 Dec 2019] in the city of Butembo in North Kivu, said the interim head of the sub-coordination of response in this city, Dr. Jean Paul Atibasi. According to him, this is a case imported from Kantine in the Mabalako health zone in Beni territory.

The sick girl was detected in a medical structure in Vulamba commune. According to the same source, some contacts have already been listed, and the decontamination measures for the health facility and the victim's household have already been taken.

The patient is on treatment at the Ebola ITAV Treatment Center. This new case comes after 55 days without a case in Butembo.

--
