Mary Marshall
<mjm2020@googlemail.com>

- Thu 19 Dec 2019. DRC: Ebola situation remains worrying in Biakato and Lwemba in Ituri
[Provinces 26 RDC, in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://www.provinces26rdc.net/rdc-la-situation-debola-reste-toujours-preoccupante-a-biakato-et-lwemba-dans-lituri/; in English https://crofsblogs.typepad.com/h5n1/2019/12/drc-ebola-situation-remains-worrying-in-biakato-and-lwemba-in-ituri.html

In Ituri, the Ebola virus disease situation remains worrying in the localities of Biakato and Lwemba in Mambasa territory. Several contact cases that have been hidden in the community are not all identified, this after dozens of community deaths from Ebola [were] recorded during the withdrawal of the response team in the area, said the provincial minister of health, Dr. Patrick Karamura.

According to him, the challenges to be met are still enormous, especially the identification of all the contact persons, 65 of whom are under surveillance in the transit centers in Biakato.

Currently, one Ebola patient and 10 suspected cases are admitted to the Biakato treatment center, he said.

Regarding the response, Dr. Patrick Karamura reassures that measures are already taken to control this epidemic, including the training of local agents for the management of Ebola cases.

Biakato civil society, for its part, believes that the support of the population for measures to combat this virus constitutes the greatest challenge to contain this epidemic.

For their involvement, the inhabitants of Lwemba asked for the rehabilitation of the local health center, which was ransacked by the militiamen in May [2019] and the recruitment of local agents in the response team. "These are the prerequisites for breaking community resistance," they say.

--
