[4] Perspective
- Wed 18 Dec 2019. Ituri: outbreak ending
[Media Congo, in French, machine trans., edited]
https://www.mediacongo.net/article-actualite-61236_ituri_le_ministre_provincial_de_la_sante_estime_que_l_epidemie_d_ebola_tend_vers_la_fin.html

In a press briefing held on Tuesday [17 Dec 2019], the provincial health minister revealed that a total of 525 positive cases of Ebola virus epidemic have been recorded in Ituri since the onset of the disease.

There have been 261 deaths reported in 9 health zones, but to date only the Mandima region in Mambasa territory continues to register new cases to date, with a positive case of the ETC (Ebola treatment center) by Byakato, which is evolving well.

Patrick Karamura also reports that 90 alert cases are followed up in the ETC of Mambasa, including 68 cases in Mambasa center, 9 in Komanda, 9 in Byakato and 3 in Bunia.

Minister Karamura, while appealing to the population for frank collaboration with the response team, believes, however, that the epidemic is coming to an end in Ituri.

"Certainly the epidemic is tending towards the end, but we must put in a lot of effort so that our province is not reassigned. We invite the public to report to the response team all alerts of suspected cases with similar signs of bleeding. I invite the entire population to collaborate with the response team to continue to detect the other cases suffering from high fevers," he explained to Bunia Actualite.

Ituri had recorded its 1st case of this deadly epidemic since September of last year [2018] in this same health area of Mandima, bordering the locality of Mangina in North Kivu, epicenter of the contagion.

